<item>
            <title>[MATH-1449] PolygonsSet.getBarycenter() returns incorrect value for empty region</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/MATH-1449</link>
                <project id="12310485" key="MATH">Commons Math</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;The o.a.c.m.geometry.euclidean.twod.PolygonsSet.getBarycenter() method returns the point (0, 0) when the region is empty. It should return (NaN, NaN) since the barycenter does not exist. This is the behavior of IntervalsSet and PolyhedronsSet.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&#160;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Pull request: &lt;a href=&quot;https://github.com/apache/commons-math/pull/80&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://github.com/apache/commons-math/pull/80&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</description>
                <environment></environment>
        <key id="13136155">MATH-1449</key>
            <summary>PolygonsSet.getBarycenter() returns incorrect value for empty region</summary>
                <type id="1" iconUrl="https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/viewavatar?size=xsmall&amp;avatarId=21133&amp;avatarType=issuetype">Bug</type>
